        "text": "A behind-the-scenes pass to one of the most beloved sci-fi comedies of all time.\n\nDon’t panic! After all, this book offers an unprecedented look into the creation of the iconic 1981 Hitchhiker’s Guide to the Galaxy BBC television series that brought Douglas Adams' extraordinary vision to the small screen.\n\nFollowing the success of the number one bestseller 42: The Wildly Improbable Ideas of Douglas Adams, this companion volume unveils Adams’ complete, never-before-published scripts of the Hitchhiker's TV series, meticulously annotated with exclusive production notes, on-set photographs, anecdotes and ephemera. Discover the intricate details of the show's development, from its innovative special effects to its most memorable performances.\n\nFeaturing exclusive interviews with Douglas Adams, the producer/director Alan J. W. Bell and the original cast and crew members, including Simon Jones, David Dixon, Mark Wing-Davey, Sandra Dickinson and Stephen Moore. Compiled by Kevin Jon Davies, a veteran of the Hitchhiker's universe who worked on the original series, this book is a treasure trove of insights and untold stories. Pop in your Babel Fish, mix yourself a Pan Galactic Gargle Blaster, sit back and enjoy.\n\nAbout Kevin Jon Davies"
